    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello,\n\nJust upgraded to `0.11` and noticing a bug when resizing my terminal.\nIssuing a `:redraw` doesn't seem to help either.\n\nI've run `nvim --clean` to avoid any issues my config may have been causing.\n\n## On 0.10\n\nNo issue, everything re-sizes correctly\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/28537767-1b03-4d86-950a-f6d929988d48\n\n## On 0.11 stable\n\nIssue exists, resizing and calling `:redraw` does not help.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/891fa065-a43c-4979-888a-dcbd01a96441\n\n## On 0.11 nightly\n\nIssue exists, resizing and calling `:redraw` does not help.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/171ce149-032a-417d-b514-9c0e179d6397\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n[add text to make it obvious]\n[resize terminal]\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nText and statusbar should be redrawn to new dimension.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
